      • sameMapCollection

        public static <K,V extends Collection> boolean sameMapCollection(Map<K,V> m1,
                                                                 Map<K,V> m2)
        Checks whether two maps contain the same mappings.
        this function specifically works on maps, where the value is a map. It compares whether both maps contain the same keys and each key map to a collection that contains the same values.
        Type Parameters:
        K - Any type of key
        V - A Map-type as Value for the maps
        Parameters:
        m1 - first map to compare
        m2 - second map to compare
        Returns:
        whether both maps are the same
